<subSubSection id="48D355CA8E64FFEC48A751F7FE2BFF5F" lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418E64FFEA48A751F7FB31F800" blockId="42.[151,1437,1755,2032]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E64FFEA48A751F7FE2BF904" bold="true" box="[151,398,1755,1780]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Description of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48E64FFEA49AD51F0FD8CF903" box="[413,553,1756,1780]" captionStart="PLATE 10" captionStartId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" captionTargetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" captionTargetId="figure-41@43.[166,1430,151,2005]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="PLATE 10. Crovettia masneri, holotype. A. Dorsal view (A) and lateral view (B). Length 2.4 mm. (From Olmi 1984)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Plate 10A, B</figureCitation>
). Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48E64FFEA4B1851F0FCDAF903" box="[808,895,1756,1780]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Head black, except mandible testaceous; antenna brown, except segments 1–2 testaceous; mesosoma and metasoma black; legs testaceous, except metacoxa basally black. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 8:4:10:8:8:6.5:5:5:5:7. Head dull, completely reticulate rugose and granulated; frontal line absent; occipital carina complete; POL = 5; OL = 3; OOL = 7; OPL = 6; TL = 8. Palpal formula of 
<typeStatus id="DF72B8E38E64FFEA49825040FDB0F874" box="[434,533,1900,1924]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
: 5/3 (on right) and 6/3 (on left). Scutum, scutellum and metanotum dull, completely reticulate rugose and granulated. Notauli absent. Propodeum reticulate rugose, without transverse or longitudinal keels. Fore wing hyaline, without dark transverse bands, with two basal cells (costal and median) completely enclosed by pigmented veins; distal part of stigmal vein shorter than proximal part (4:6). Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<caption id="54B656C98E65FFEB48A750E6FAEDF811" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278404" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5278404" box="[151,1352,1994,2017]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278404/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" startId="43.[151,233,1994,2017]" targetBox="[186,1414,186,1982]" targetPageId="43">
<paragraph id="007606418E65FFEB48A750E6FAEDF811" blockId="43.[151,1352,1994,2017]" box="[151,1352,1994,2017]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E65FFEB48A750E6FEAAF811" bold="true" box="[151,271,1994,2017]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">PLATE 10.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="C7C97DC28E65FFEB492550E7FE69F811" baseAuthorityName="Olmi" baseAuthorityYear="1984" box="[277,460,1995,2017]" class="Insecta" family="Dryinidae" genus="Crovettia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masneri">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E65FFEB492550E7FE69F811" box="[277,460,1995,2017]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Crovettia masneri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype. 
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E65FFEB4A0E50E6FDF2F811" bold="true" box="[574,599,1994,2017]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">A.</emphasis>
Dorsal view (
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E65FFEB4AD750E6FD5CF811" bold="true" box="[743,761,1994,2017]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">A</emphasis>
) and lateral view (
<emphasis id="32BDDA538E65FFEB4B8850E7FC6CF810" bold="true" box="[952,969,1995,2016]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">B</emphasis>
). Length 2.4 mm. (From 
<bibRefCitation id="64587BB08E65FFEB4CFC50E7FA98F811" author="Olmi" box="[1228,1341,1995,2017]" firstAuthor="Olmi" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 1913" refId="ref364993" refString="Olmi, M. (1984) A revision of the Dryinidae (Hymenoptera). Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 37, I - XII + 1 - 1913." type="journal article" year="1984">Olmi 1984</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
